### Memoize Column Definitions (React/TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/packages/features/data-table/GUIDE.md

Demonstrates how to effectively memoize column definitions within a React component using the `useMemo` hook. This is crucial for performance by preventing unnecessary re-renders of column configurations. It relies on React's hook system and TypeScript for type safety.

```tsx
const columns = useMemo(
  () => [
    {
      id: "name",
      header: "Name",
      accessorKey: "name",
      meta: { type: ColumnFilterType.TEXT },
    },
  ],
  []
);
```

